{
  "_doc": "Outlaws of Thunder Junction (OTJ) Play + Collector recipes from Wizards' official 'Collecting Outlaws of Thunder Junction' article (https://magic.wizards.com/en/news/feature/collecting-outlaws-of-thunder-junction). OTJ shipped Play + Collector boosters only — NO Draft Booster — so authoritative is true and draft is intentionally undefined. Sub-set codes: OTJ = main set, OTP = Breaking News (bonus sheet), BIG = The Big Score, OTC = OTJ Commander, SPG = Special Guests. Exact rates published for The List replacement (20%), the wildcard rare/mythic rate (1 in 12), Booster Fun rate (2.5%), the Breaking News rare/mythic rate (1 in 3), the land slot, the token/art slot, and the Collector premium-foil slot are used verbatim. Approximations: The List card modeled as a special_guest outcome against OTP (no dedicated List filter); rare-vs-mythic splits inside the wildcard, foil, Booster Fun, OTP, OTC, and premium slots are not published per-card and are estimated with standard splits; 'wanted poster' and 'vault frame' frame treatments have no dedicated filter and use the nearest of showcase / borderless / extended_art; western landscape & regular basics via basic_land. Specific finishes re-pointed to dedicated filters: in the Premium Foil Special Slot the 'Textured Foil Breaking News' outcome now uses textured_foil and the 'Raised Foil Vault Frame' outcome now uses raised_foil, instead of the showcase stand-in. AUDIT 2026-06 (article re-verification): the commons slot previously gave EVERY one of the 5 common sub-pulls a 20% List chance (≈63% of packs with a List card, ~1 per pack on average) and pointed the outcome at OTP (Breaking News). The article says 20% of PLAY BOOSTERS contain one List card, and OTJ-era “The List” comprises The Big Score (BIG) + Special Guests (SPG). Re-modeled per-slot: 96% common / 3% BIG / 1% SPG (20%/5 slots, split ~3:1 by sheet size 30 BIG : 10 SPG).",
